prompt:
Add a public function called Countdown to Effects.calr that counts down from 5 to 1 using a while loop. The function takes no parameters and returns void. It needs the console write effect.

Use this exact Calor while-loop syntax:
§F{f001:Countdown:pub}
  §O{void}
  §E{cw}
  §B{count} 5
  §WH{w001} (> count 0)
    §C{Console.WriteLine}
      §A count
    §/C
    §ASSIGN count (- count 1)
  §/WH{w001}
§/F{f001}

The §WH{id} (condition) syntax creates a while loop where:
- id is a unique loop identifier (w001)
- condition is evaluated each iteration
- §B{name} expr creates a variable binding
- §ASSIGN name expr assigns a new value
